Just got the album by July Talk. Iam really liking it. Their bio describes them as,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Imagine Tom Waits and Amy Millan shouting whiskey-soaked lullabies while backed by the members of Crazy Horse and youʼd have a good start. Striking a frenzied balance between Americana and dance-floor-filling indie-rock, July Talkʻs Beauty and the Beast aesthetic burns a little going down, but is sure to warm your belly &amp;hellip;
It is a greatalbuma nd they are playing live in glasgow, &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.kingtuts.co.uk/gig-listings/&#34;&gt;King Tuts Wah Wah Hut&lt;/a&gt;, on Tuesday next week, (30th September). It should be a good evening. If you fancy it, Shout.
